{
  "html": "<div id=\"BUV\" class=\"uplift front\">\n    <section id=\"course-front-body\" class=\"responsive-padding\" style=\"color: #2d3b45; background: none; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px;\">\n        <article id=\"course-lesson-intro-text\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em;\">\n            <h3 class=\"heavy\" style=\"margin: 0; font-size: 2.7em;\">Development for Games Essentials</h3>\n            <p>This module introduces the key concepts required to facilitate balanced and tested game designs. Studying the language and application of game mechanics will help you assess the construction of the production side of gameplay, seeing how different elements within a game environment interact with one another to form the whole. </p>\n        </article>\n        <div class=\"grid-row\">\n            <article class=\"col-lg-4 buv-responsive-video-100\" style=\"padding-left: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 20px;\"><iframe style=\"background: lightgrey;\"></iframe></article>\n            <article class=\"col-lg-8\" style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding-left: 12px;\">\n                <h3><strong>Module Outcomes:</strong></h3>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Develop an understanding of the language of mechanics and metrics abstracted from the theme and setting of games.</p>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Effectively use mechanics and metrics to identify and adjust the balance in games.</p>\n                <p><span style=\"color: #ba372a; font-size: 14pt;\">+ &nbsp;</span>Identify and compare research methods appropriate to accomplishing specific research goals.</p>\n            </article>\n        </div>\n    </section>\n</div>\n<div class=\"grid-row responsive-padding\" style=\"padding-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0px; margin-bottom: -50px;\">\n    <h3 style=\"padding-left: 12px;\"><strong>Module Content:</strong></h3>\n</div>",
